definition: cat/CL:隻|只[zhi1]/(dialect) to hide oneself/(coll.) modem

sentences.english: The Jaguar is said to be the longest-lived species of cat, sometimes reaching 30 years.
sentences.chinese: 據說豹貓能活得最久，有些貓能活到30歲。

sentences.english: Ocelots have no need for such fancy cameras.
sentences.chinese: 豹貓不需要這種先進攝影機。

sentences.english: Fishing cats are so similar in size and weight to the Ocelot, we couldn't split them up.
sentences.chinese: 漁貓的體型和體重都和豹貓十分相似，我們很難分辨。

sentences.english: The only consolation about being caught by an Ocelot is that you never see them coming.
sentences.chinese: 被豹貓抓到唯一的安慰，是你絕對看不到它接近。

sentences.english: The wall also blocks the daily rounds of ocelots, another member of the cat family.
sentences.chinese: 隔離牆還妨礙了另一種貓族成員豹貓的日常活動。

definition: Aerodramus, genus of birds that use echolocation, a subset of the Collocaliini tribe (swiflets), two of whose species – Aerodramus fuciphagus and Aerodramus maximus – build nests harvested to make bird's nest soup
the breeding season (zool.)/oestrus (period of sexual receptivity of female mammals)
